questions.specification:
A continuous random variable $Y$ has the probability density function $g$ given by

$$
g(y)=\begin{cases}
\frac{\pi y}{36} \sin \left(\frac{\pi y}{6}\right), & 0 \leqslant y \leqslant 6 \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

The continuous random variable $Y$ has probability density function $g$ given by

$$
g(y) = \begin{cases}
3by, & 0 \leqslant y < 0.5 \\
b(2 - y), & 0.5 \leqslant y < 2 \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

The continuous random variable Y has a probability density function given by

$$
g(y) = \left\{ 
\begin{array}{ll}
m\cos (\frac{\pi y}{6}),& 0 \leq y \leq 3 \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{array} 
\right.
$$
